title: Date of the contract

title: Specified entity Party B

title: Specified transaction scope
explanation: The text specifies amendments to the definition of 'Specified Transaction' in Section 14, including insertion of 'margin loan' and inclusion of clearing agreements, indicating non-standard changes to Section 14.

title: Cross default applicable parties
explanation: The text states that the 'Cross-Default' provisions of Section 5(a)(vi) will apply, which generally applies to both parties (Party A and Party B) in an ISDA Master Agreement.

title: Specified indebtness includes borrowed_money
explanation: No mention of borrowed money being included in Specified Indebtedness; only deposits are explicitly excluded.

title: Specified indebtness excludes deposits
explanation: Text explicitly states Specified Indebtedness shall exclude deposits received in the ordinary course of business.

title: Party for calculation agent
explanation: Section (6)(i) states that the Calculation Agent will be Party A, except if an Event of Default occurs and is continuing in respect of Party A, then it will be Party B or an Independent Dealer. The default party is Party A.

title: Governing Law
